{"actor":{"display":"Evin Tunador","id":"evintunador@gmail.com","type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"1\t---\n2\tname: project-cledger-reanchor-task\n3\tdescription: \"re-anchor shipped in 0.8.0 (four local commits, unpushed as of 2026-07-20); what remains and the design decisions behind it\"\n4\tmetadata: \n5\t  node_type: memory\n6\t  type: project\n7\t  originSessionId: 4c1ed024-2edf-45b6-8cbb-ee40a5ebadc3\n8\t  modified: 2026-07-21T17:35:57.193Z\n9\t---\n10\t\n11\tRe-anchor shipped 2026-07-20 as 0.8.0 in four commits (d3934db, c36b4b5, a452048, 5581e31 — local, not pushed). Originally mis-scoped by a prior session's handoff prompt as post-push purge; purge remains a separate unshipped roadmap item ([[project-cledger-redaction-state]]).\n12\t\n13\tDesign decisions (user-confirmed): append-only `re_anchor` mapping events, never moving notes (union merge would resurrect removals); anchored to the successor commit so mappings ride the surviving DAG; deterministic identity (sorted SHAs, system actor, successor's committer timestamp as occurred_at) so two machines' detections dedup; read-time fixpoint resolution handles chained rewrites; detection = tree equality fast-path + `git patch-id --stable` over -U0 diffs (cumulative for squash, per-commit for rebase), auto-applied on read gated by a target-tip cursor, exact matches only — ambiguity is surfaced, never guessed; `cledger re-anchor` command for dry-run/--apply/manual `--onto` (human actor, GC'd full SHAs accepted verbatim).\n14\t\n15\tSuggestion tier shipped 2026-07-21 as 0.9.0 (commits 61c9c89..8e6bf37, unpushed): forge abstraction in src/forge/ (GitHub driver shells out to the user's `gh` session, 10s timeout, degrades to null — user chose gh over token config), evidence tiers (0: forge merge-commit assertion verified locally; 1: \"(#N)\" subject + squash-message-lists-branch-subjects corroboration; 2: per-file patch-id overlap), confirm-only via printed `--onto` command, forge queried only in the ex