{"actor":{"id":"claude-sonnet-5","type":"agent"},"content":{"blocks":[{"caller":{"type":"direct"},"id":"toolu_01XrHoZZPkM6EkbChVh8WZod","input":{"content":"---\nname: project-cledger-reasoning-preservation\ndescription: \"Preserve provider-encrypted reasoning as opaque state shipped in cledger 0.10.0 (2026-07-22, uncommitted at time of writing); design decisions and deliberate scope cuts\"\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nRoadmap item from [[project-ledger-ecosystem]] (\"Preserve provider-encrypted reasoning as opaque state\") implemented 2026-07-22 as cledger 0.10.0 — schema.ts, src/adapters/drift.ts, src/adapters/codex.ts, src/cli.ts changed; working tree edited but not yet committed as of this writing (user hadn't asked to commit).\n\nProblem: Codex's `reasoning` response_items carry `encrypted_content` only OpenAI can decrypt; cledger previously dropped them outright. Turnbridge's `scripts/probe-encrypted-reasoning.mjs` proved replaying the raw blob back through the API restores the model's hidden reasoning — same-account AND cross-account (different paid ChatGPT account, identical token accounting, ciphertext not keyed per-account). Dropping the blob forecloses ever restoring reasoning when a Codex-origin conversation is fabricated back into Codex elsewhere.\n\nDesign decisions (user-confirmed 2026-07-22, after I corrected two of my own mistaken framings — see below):\n- New dedicated `reasoning` kind added to `KNOWN_KINDS`, not a reuse of `unrecognized` and not folded into the adjacent `conversation_turn`'s raw — `unrecognized` means \"not yet understood, may be renormalized later\"; `reasoning` ciphertext is *permanently* opaque, no future cledger version will ever decrypt it. Kind is provider-agnostic (not \"codex_reasoning\") since other CLIs may expose the same shape later.\n- Event shape (`reasoningDraft` in drift.ts, used by codex.ts): `actor: {type: \"agent\"}`, `content: {opaque: true}` only, full source line under `raw.data`. Same idempotency trick as `unrecognizedDraft` — `conversation.seq` in the identity subset makes re-scans dedup even though `content` is a constant.\n- Sync: rides the ledger's existing default-on transport, no special carve-out — despite my initial (wrong) framing that sync was \"opt-in\" by ecosystem convention. It is not; see the correction in [[project-ledger-ecosystem]]. User picked this after I corrected myself.\n- Visibility: `cledger export` (lossless dump) includes `reasoning` events by default, unchanged. `cledger log`/`show` (human-facing transcript views) hide them by default — new `--with-reasoning` flag reveals, as does an explicit `--kind reasoning` on log. This required new filtering logic (`includeReasoning`/`hideOpaqueReasoning` in cli.ts) since no prior kind was ever hidden by default.\n- Forward-only: sessions captured before 0.10.0 already lost their reasoning permanently; no backfill/rescan of old rollout files was built. User explicitly chose this over backfilling.\n- Deliberately NOT touched: `agent_message` inter-agent messages still strip embedded `encrypted_content` blocks outright (drop, not preserve) — same provider-withheld material, but embedded mid-line rather than a standalone response_item, so folding it into the new `reasoning` kind needs its own shape decision. Flagged in README roadmap as a follow-up, not silently expanded into this cut.\n- Open questions left to turnbridge, not cledger: blob TTL, API-platform-org auth parity (only ChatGPT-account cross-account replay is verified so far).\n\nProcess note for future sessions: when a memory (here, [[project-ledger-ecosystem]]'s \"explicit opt-in sync\" line) makes a specific factual claim about current shipped behavior, verify it against the README/code before using it to frame a question to the user — the user caught this one by pushing back rather than accepting my framing.\n","file_path":"/Users/evintunador/.claude/projects/-Users-evintunador-repos-evintunador-conversation-ledger/memory/project-cledger-reasoning-preservation.md"},"name":"Write","type":"tool_use"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"4b958730eec664173debd21e6aaa53f76db71747f7e61fe3c37269b5ad5d9f2b","head":"d6705ff7ea32c092c92aefdf69cb6a80e7902a24","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:ca50d7db-8621-495c-a94a-c3d3ab731073","seq":282},"id":"ev1-f77d28ede81cd1cde8b8f03c27a40b234dad375714a02b128f15822104a6431d","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-22T18:31:16.934Z","producer":{"session_id":"ca50d7db-8621-495c-a94a-c3d3ab731073","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.10.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","effort":"high","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"caller":{"type":"direct"},"id":"toolu_01XrHoZZPkM6EkbChVh8WZod","input":{"content":"---\nname: project-cledger-reasoning-preservation\ndescription: \"Preserve provider-encrypted reasoning as opaque state shipped in cledger 0.10.0 (2026-07-22, uncommitted at time of writing); design decisions and deliberate scope cuts\"\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nRoadmap item from [[project-ledger-ecosystem]] (\"Preserve provider-encrypted reasoning as opaque state\") implemented 2026-07-22 as cledger 0.10.0 — schema.ts, src/adapters/drift.ts, src/adapters/codex.ts, src/cli.ts changed; working tree edited but not yet committed as of this writing (user hadn't asked to commit).\n\nProblem: Codex's `reasoning` response_items carry `encrypted_content` only OpenAI can decrypt; cledger previously dropped them outright. Turnbridge's `scripts/probe-encrypted-reasoning.mjs` proved replaying the raw blob back through the API restores the model's hidden reasoning — same-account AND cross-account (different paid ChatGPT account, identical token accounting, ciphertext not keyed per-account). Dropping 